README.md

Awesome

   [https://www.raspberrypi.org/]Raspberry Pi Logo

     The Raspberry Pi is a series of credit card-sized single-board
     computers developed in the United Kingdom by the Raspberry Pi
     Foundation to promote the teaching of basic computer science in
     schools and developing countries. Official Link:
     [https://raspberrypi.org/]Raspberry Pi Homepage

   This list is a collection of tools, projects, images and resources
   conforming to the
   [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome/blob/master/awesome.md]Awesome
   Manifesto

   Contributions very welcome but first see
   [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-raspberry
   -pi#contributing]Contributing

Contents

     * Models
     * OS Images
     * Tools
     * Projects
     * Resources

Models

   The complete collection of Raspberry Pi models consist of:
     * Raspberry Pi 1, Model A & Model B (2012, discontinued)
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-1-model-b-plus/]
       Raspberry Pi 1, Model B+ (July, 2014)
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-1-model-a-plus/]
       Raspberry Pi 1, Model A+ (November, 2014)
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-2-model-b/]Raspb
       erry Pi 2, Model B (February, 2015)
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-zero/]Raspberry
       Pi Zero (November, 2015)
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-3-model-b/]Raspb
       erry Pi 3, Model B (March, 2016)
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-zero-w/]Raspberr
       y Pi Zero W (February, 2017)
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-3-model-b-plus/]
       Raspberry Pi 3, Model B+ (March, 2018)

OS Images

     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/raspbian/]Raspbian - The
       official supported Raspberry Pi OS, based on Debian and available
       as a lite version.
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/noobs/]NOOBS - New Out Of
       the Box Software, an easy OS installer for beginners.
     * [https://ubuntu-mate.org/raspberry-pi/]Ubuntu MATE - Ubuntu
       distribution for the Raspberry Pi based on MATE desktop.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-2+.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://developer.ubuntu.com/core/get-started/raspberry-pi-2-3]Sna
       ppy Ubuntu Core - Official (minimal) Ubuntu distribution for IoT.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-2+.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://developer.microsoft.com/nl-nl/windows/iot/Downloads.htm]Wi
       ndows 10 IoT Core - Windows 10 distribution for IoT.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-2+.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://osmc.tv/]OSMC - Open Source Media Centre, based on Kodi.
     * [http://pinet.org.uk/]PiNet - System to manage Raspberry Pi
       classrooms.
     * [https://www.riscosopen.org/content/downloads/raspberry-pi]Risc OS
       - Non-Linux OS originated from the group that developed the ARM
       microprocessor.
     * [http://www.runeaudio.com/]RuneAudio - Free and open source OS that
       turns embedded hardware into Hi-Fi music players.
     * [http://openelec.tv/]OpenELEC - Open Embedded Linux Entertainment
       Center, a very lightweight Kodi build.
     * [http://blog.hypriot.com/about/]HypriotOS - Minimal Debian-based
       operating system, optimized to run Docker.
     * [https://www.offensive-security.com/kali-linux-arm-images/]Kali
       Linux - Penetration Testing & Ethical Hacking Linux distro for ARM
       devices.
     * [https://retropie.org.uk/]RetroPie - Retro-gaming on the Raspberry
       Pi.
     * [https://wiki.alpinelinux.org/wiki/Raspberry_Pi]Alpine Linux -
       Security-oriented, lightweight Linux distribution based on musl
       libc and busybox.
     * [https://archlinuxarm.org/]Arch Linux ARM - Lightweight and
       flexible Linux distribution that tries to Keep It Simple.
     * [https://volumio.org/]Volumio - Headless audiophile music player,
       designed to play music with the highest possible fidelity.
     * [https://www.recalbox.com/]Recalbox - Drag & drop light-weight
       retro-gaming and media center on the Raspberry Pi.
     * [http://lakka.tv/]Lakka - Retro-gaming on the Raspberry Pi built
       entirely on RetroArch.
     * [http://www.rasplex.com/]RasPlex - Plex client for the Raspberry
       Pi.
     * [https://github.com/futurice/chilipie-kiosk]chilipie-kiosk - Image
       which boots directly into full-screen Chrome, perfect for
       dashboards and build monitors.
       Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://github.com/Fourdee/DietPi]DietPi - Minimal image designed
       to fit on a 2GB SD card, with tons of configurable settings and
       scripts.
     * [https://wiki.centos.org/SpecialInterestGroup/AltArch/Arm32/Raspber
       ryPi3]CentOS - CentOS on the Raspberry Pi.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-2+.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://minibianpi.wordpress.com/]Minibian - Minimal Raspbian
       (lighter than Jessie Lite).
     * [http://www.berryterminal.com/doku.php/berryboot]BerryBoot -
       Bootloader/universal OS installer, with support to VNC and
       HDMI-CEC.
     * [https://piratebox.cc/raspberry_pi:diy]PirateBox - Anonymous
       offline mobile file-sharing and communications system.
     * [https://octopi.octoprint.org/]OctoPi - Distribution for 3d
       printers.
     * [http://developers.kano.me/downloads/]Kano OS - Open-source OS for
       exploration, creation, and play - free for Raspberry Pi and the new
       Pi 3.
     * [https://resinos.io/]resinOS - open source OS to run Docker
       containers on embedded devices that's been designed for reliability
       and proven in production.
     * [https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Raspberry_Pi#Preparing_the_SD_card]
       Fedora - Linux Fedora distribution built for the Pi.
       Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://github.com/ccrisan/motioneyeos/wiki]motionEyeOS - Linux
       distribution that turns a single-board computer into a video
       surveillance system.
     * [https://ownyourbits.com/2017/02/13/nextcloud-ready-raspberry-pi-im
       age/]NextCloudPi - Nextcloud ready image based on Raspbian.
       Features Nextcloud 11 running on Raspbian 8, with PHP 7 and HTTP2
       enabled Apache server.
     * [http://pideck.com/]PiDeck - Small form factor DVS system allowing
       you to control digital music files with timecode vinyl.
     * [https://wiki.openwrt.org/toh/raspberry_pi_foundation/raspberry_pi]
       OpenWRT - OpenWrt is described as a Linux distribution for embedded
       devices for network management.
     * [https://wiki.freebsd.org/FreeBSD/arm/Raspberry%20Pi]FreeBSD -
       FreeBSD is an advanced computer operating system used to power
       modern servers, desktops, and embedded platforms.
     * [https://wiki.netbsd.org/ports/evbarm/raspberry_pi/]NetBSD - NetBSD
       is a free, fast, secure, and highly portable Unix-like Open Source
       operating system.
     * [https://home-assistant.io/hassio/installation/]Hass.io - Home
       automation operating system/application for embedded device, also
       available standalone.
     * [https://developer.android.com/things/hardware/raspberrypi.html]And
       roid Things - Build connected devices for a wide variety of
       consumer, retail, and industrial applications.
       Supports Raspberry Pi 3
     * [https://gladysproject.com/en/]Gladys Project - Gladys, Your home
       assistant.
       Supports Raspberry Pi 3
     * [https://www.openmediavault.org/]OpenMediaVault - OpenMediaVault is
       the next generation network attached storage (NAS) solution based
       on Debian Linux containing services like SSH, (S)FTP, SMB/CIFS,
       DAAP media server, RSync, BitTorrent client and many more.
       Supports Raspberry Pi 3
     * [https://github.com/bortek/EZ-WifiBroadcast/wiki]EZ-WifiBroadcast -
       Affordable Wireless Digital HD Video Transmission made easy.
       Supports Raspberry Pi 3
       Supports Raspberry Pi Zero
     * [https://github.com/seeul8er/DroneBridge]DroneBridge - A
       WifiBroadcast extension to make for a real alternative to DJI
       Lightbridge and other similar systems.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-3.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 3
     * [https://www.trueos.org/trueos-pico/]TrueOS - FreeBSD-based thin
       client solution.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-2+.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://docs.openhab.org/installation/openhabian.html]OpenHABian -
       A preconfigured version of the OpenHAB home automation software.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-2+.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://mariolukas.github.io/FabScanPi-Server/]FabScanPi -
       FabScanPi is an open source 3D laser scanner using the Raspberry Pi
       Camera Module.
       Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://rocketshow.net/]Rocket Show - Play synced backing tracks,
       videos and DMX light-sequences live on stage.
       Supports Raspberry Pi 3

Tools

     * [http://www.pibakery.org/]PiBakery - The blocks based, easy to use
       setup tool for Raspberry Pi.
     * [http://www.tweaking4all.com/software/macosx-software/macosx-apple-
       pi-baker/]ApplePi Bakery - macOS application to easily
       install/backup/restore images onto an SD card.
     * [https://www.etcher.io/]Etcher - SD card burner app that is simple
       for end users, extensible for developers, and works on any
       platform.
     * [https://github.com/Drewsif/PiShrink/]PiShrink - Bash script that
       automatically shrinks a pi image that will then resize to the max
       size of the SD card on boot.
     * [https://github.com/StarshipEngineer/OpenVPN-Setup]OpenVPN-Setup -
       Shell script to set up Raspberry Pi as an OpenVPN server.
     * [https://github.com/RPi-Distro/pi-gen]pi-gen - Tool used to create
       the raspberrypi.org Raspbian images. This can be used to create
       your own custom images with specific packages installed, etc.
     * [http://www.pivpn.io/]PiVPN - Simple, Flexible, and Managable
       single line install of OpenVPN Server for your Raspberry Pi.
     * [https://github.com/initialstate/pi-sensor-free-presence-detector/w
       iki]Network Presence Detector - Setup a Pi Zero to scan for devices
       on a WiFi network and use that to determine who is "home".
     * [https://github.com/resin-io-playground/resin-bridge]Resin Bridge -
       Simple application/repo to bridge a Raspberry Pi's wlan0 interface
       to devices plugged into it over ethernet (eth0).
     * [https://steveedson.co.uk/tools/wpa/]WiFi config generator - Simple
       tool to generate wpa_supplicant.conf files with wifi settings
     * [https://ownyourbits.com/2017/02/06/raspbian-on-qemu-with-network-a
       ccess/]Raspbian QEMU with network - Simple tool to launch QEMU on
       Raspbian with the required modifications on the system and kernel.
       Automatic network access. Handy to create images in your PC.
     * [https://github.com/billz/raspap-webgui]RaspAP-webgui - A simple,
       responsive web interface to control wifi, hostapd and related
       services on the Raspberry Pi.
     * [https://github.com/Protocentral/HealthyPi]HealthyPi - HAT which
       includes vital health monitoring like ECG, respiration, pulse
       oximetry and optional blood pressure & body temperature sensing.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-2+.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 2+
     * [https://github.com/samyk/poisontap]PoisonTap - Exploits
       locked/password protected computers over USB, drops persistent
       WebSocket-based backdoor, exposes internal router, and siphons
       cookies using Raspberry Pi Zero & Node.js.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-0.png]Supports Raspberry Pi Zero
     * [https://github.com/mame82/P4wnP1]P4wnP1 - P4wnP1 is a highly
       customizable USB attack platform, based on a low cost Raspberry Pi
       Zero or Raspberry Pi Zero W (required for HID backdoor).
       Supports Raspberry Pi Zero
     * [https://cusdeb.com/en/]CusDeb - Web UI for creating custom images
       with specific packages installed.
     * [https://github.com/farjump/raspberry-pi]Alpha - Remotely load,
       debug and test bare-metal programs using GDB with this system-level
       GDB server.
     * [https://github.com/tolstoyevsky/pieman]Pieman - Script for
       creating custom images based on Raspbian, Devuan and Ubuntu.
     * [https://github.com/cjimti/iotwifi]iotwifi - Wifi AP + Client
       management in 8MB [https://hub.docker.com/r/cjimti/iotwifi/]Docker
       Container, with REST API for controlling wifi client and station
       modes simultaneously.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-3.png]Supports Raspberry Pi 3

Projects

     * [https://cdn-learn.adafruit.com/downloads/pdf/mini-oontz-3d-printed
       -midi-controller.pdf]Mini OONTZ - 3D printed mini MIDI controller.
     * [https://hackaday.com/2012/10/04/malicious-raspberry-pi-power-strip
       -looks-a-bit-scary/]Power Sniffing Strip - Enclosure in a power
       strip, sniffing network data.
     * [https://medium.com/@pieterjan_m/erlang-pi2-arm-cluster-vs-xeon-vm-
       40871d35d356#.bpao66cm8]Raspberry Pi Erlang Cluster - Erlang
       cluster on a Raspberry Pi 2.
     * [http://www.mjoldfield.com/atelier/2012/08/ntp-nixie.html]NTP
       driven Nixie Clock - Nixie Tube Clock powered by a Raspberry Pi.
     * [http://hackaday.com/2014/02/17/40-node-raspi-cluster/]40-node
       Raspberry Pi Cluster - Cluster aimed to be under the size of full
       tower desktop.
     * [http://www.widriksson.com/raspberry-pi-hadoop-cluster/]Raspberry
       PI Hadoop Cluster - Big Data cluster running on the Raspberry Pi.
     * [http://www.datastax.com/dev/blog/32-node-raspberry-pi-cassandra-cl
       uster]Multi-Datacenter Cassandra on 32 Raspberry Pi's - Showcase
       for the always on, fault tolerant nature of Cassandra using a
       Raspberry Pi cluster board.
     * [http://bryanapperson.com/blog/the-definitive-guide-ceph-cluster-on
