Resources

Articles

     * [https://www.liquidlight.co.uk/blog/article/raspberry-pi-what-is-it
       -and-why-do-i-need-one/]Raspberry Pi and why do I need one? - Intro
       into the Raspberry Pi and what can be done with it.
     * [https://raspberrypi.about.com/od/Power/tp/10-Ways-to-Power-your-Ra
       spberry-Pi.htm]10 Ways To Power - Information about different &
       correct ways to power the pi.
     * [http://www.nhatqbui.com/assets/TheUltimateRaspberryPiSecurityGuide
       .pdf]The Ultimate Raspberry Pi Security Guide - Extensive guide on
       security best practices for the Pi ie. exposed to the internet.
     * [https://github.com/wtsxDev/Raspberry-Pi]Raspberry Pi A to Z List -
       Comprehensive list with links to common questions & pitfalls.

Tutorials

     * [https://blog.thibmaekelbergh.be/post/bridging-wifi-to-the-raspberr
       y-pi-over-ethernet]Bridging Wifi to the Raspberry Pi over Ethernet
       - Set up tethered networking between macOS & Raspberry Pi.
     * [https://blog.thibmaekelbergh.be/post/raspberry-pi-login-with-ssh-k
       eys]Raspberry Pi login with SSH keys - Password-less login for ssh
       sessions on the Raspberry Pi.
     * [http://blog.hsp.dk/how-to-setup-vpn-server-on-raspberry-pi-or-digi
       talocean/]How to setup a secure VPN server on Raspberry Pi or
       DigitalOcean - Simple, secure and detailed guide to setup VPN on
       your Raspberry Pi.
     * [https://thesocietea.org/2016/03/controlling-spotify-with-slack-and
       -a-raspberry-pi/]Controlling Spotify with Slack and a Raspberry Pi
       - Node.js project to control Spotify & Slack with libspotify.
     * [https://github.com/irtimmer/moonlight-embedded]Moonlight - Nvidia
       GameStream implementation to stream your full collection of Steam
       games from desktop to the Raspberry Pi.
     * [http://blog.gbaman.info/?p=791]Raspberry Pi Zero: Programming over
       USB - Guide to boot and access a Raspberry Pi Zero over a USB cable
       without need of an ethernet/wifi connection, keyboard or screen.
       Supports Raspberry Pi Zero
     * [https://www.mikestreety.co.uk/blog/use-a-raspberry-pi-with-multipl
       e-wifi-networks]Use a Raspberry Pi with multiple WiFi networks -
       Tutorial on using a Raspberry Pi with multiple networks.
     * [http://www.htpcguides.com/category/raspberry-pi/]Raspberry Pi
       Media Server Guides - Media Server and NAS tutorials from HTPC
       Guides.
     * [https://n-o-d-e.net/pi_zero_dongle.html]Turn the Raspberry Pi Zero
       into a mini dongle computer - Setup a pi0 to be able to ssh & vnc
       over USB.
       [file://localhost/thibmaek/awesome-raspberry-pi/blob/master/media/b
       adges/rpi-0.png]Supports Raspberry Pi Zero
     * [http://developer.radiusnetworks.com/2014/04/27/how-to-make-a-raspb
       erry-pi-turn-on-a-lamp-with-an-ibeacon.html]How To Make a Raspberry
       Pi Turn on a Lamp with iBeacon(TM) Technology - Good
       beginners-guide to working with Beacon technology.
     * [https://raymii.org/s/articles/Build_a_35_dollar_Time_Capsule_-_Ras
       pberry_Pi_Time_Machine.html]Build a $35 Time Capsule - Time Machine
       Backup Server.
     * [https://lifehacker.com/how-to-turn-your-raspberry-pi-into-a-retro-
       game-console-498561192]Raspberry Pi Game Console - How to Build a
       Raspberry Pi Retro Game Console for $35.
     * [https://aaron.haurwitz.com/#!/posts/raspberry-pi-docker-swarm-with
       -lets-encrypt]Docker Swarm with LetsEncrypt - Clear guidelines on
       how to set up a cluster with Docker, distributing services with
       Docker Compose and signing valid SSL certs with Letsencrypt.
     * [http://hackaday.com/2017/06/14/diy-raspberry-neural-network-sees-a
       ll-recognizes-some/]DIY Neural Network - Uses image recognition and
       Google's Inception to recognize specific objects.
     * [https://www.codedonut.com/raspberry-pi/raspberry-pi-plex-media-ser
       ver/]Turn a Raspberry Pi into a Plex Media Server - Beginners guide
       to setting up a Plex media server to stream all of your media
       content.

